# Manukai Design Issues Guide

> Reference document for creating Product Design issues in the `CAM-Copilot/frontend-application` repository.

---

## Overview

This guide defines the structure and labeling system for Product Design related issues in Manukai. Use this as a reference when creating issues via GitHub or with an LLM assistant.

---

## Issue Types

Design issues cover the following categories:

| Type               | Description                                         |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------- |
| **Research**       | User interviews, user tests, discovery sessions     |
| **Feature Design** | Designing new features, concepts, explorations      |
| **Improvement**    | Enhancing existing features                         |
| **Clarification**  | Edge cases, specs, "what happens when..." questions |
| **Design System**  | Components, tokens, patterns, documentation         |
| **Visual**         | Polish, icons, illustrations, motion, styling       |

---

## Labels

### Type Labels (pick one)

| Label            | Use for                               |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `design`         | Base label ‚Äì add to ALL design issues |
| `research`       | Interviews, user tests, discovery     |
| `feature-design` | New feature designs                   |
| `improvement`    | Enhancing existing features           |
| `clarification`  | Edge cases, specs, detail decisions   |
| `design-system`  | Components, tokens, patterns          |
| `visual`         | Polish, icons, illustrations          |

### Priority Labels (optional)

| Label       | Meaning                                  |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `Prio 1` üî¥ | Critical ‚Äì blocking or urgent for client |
| `Prio 2` üü° | Important ‚Äì should be addressed soon     |
| `Prio 3` üü¢ | Nice to have ‚Äì backlog                   |

---

## Issue Template

```markdown
## Source

- üí° Product discovery
- üè¢ Client feedback / Research
- üîß Engineering team

**Client:** [if applicable, free text e.g. "Bosch", "PSI", "Straumann"]
**Reported by:** [name of person who reported/requested]

---

## Description

[Short description of the issue, idea, or request]

---

## Affected Area

[e.g., Feature Assignment, Similar Search, Operation Management, Batch Processing, Project Management, 3D Viewer, PDF Viewer, Filtering, Quality of Life, Performance, Design System]

---

## Screenshot / Image (optional)

[Drag & drop image into GitHub, or add image URL]
```

---

## Source Definitions

| Source                        | When to use                                                                                                                                   |
| ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **üí° Product discovery**      | Internal ideation from design or product team                                                                                                 |
| **üî¨ UX Research / Feedback** | Insight from user interviews, usability tests, or observation ,Request, bug report, or idea came from a customer. Always include client name. |
| **üîß Engineering team**       | Feedback or question from developers during implementation                                                                                    |

---

## Affected Areas (Examples)

Common areas in Manukai to reference:

| Area                     | Description                                               |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Feature Assignment**   | Assigning dimensions, tolerances, properties to features  |
| **Similar Search**       | Finding similar features/programs, comparison views       |
| **Operation Management** | Operations workflow, adding/editing/reordering operations |
| **Batch Processing**     | Multi-feature handling, bulk tool replacement             |
| **Project Management**   | Project overview, loading parts, history, states          |
| **3D Viewer**            | Gizmo, model visualization, face selection                |
| **PDF Viewer**           | Drawing viewer, OCR rectangles, annotations               |
| **Filtering**            | Search criteria, parameter filters, filter UI             |
| **Quality of Life**      | Tooltips, keyboard shortcuts, small UX improvements       |
| **Performance**          | Loading states, animations, speed optimizations           |
| **Design System**        | Components, tokens, patterns, icons                       |
| **Navigation**           | Sidebar, routing, screen transitions                      |
| **Settings**             | Account, preferences, configuration                       |

---

## Example Issues

### Example 1: Client feedback for improvement

**Title:** Improve tolerance input ‚Äì allow typing custom values

**Labels:** `design`, `improvement`, `Prio 2`

```markdown
## Source

üî¨User research / Feedback

**Client:** PSI
**Reported by:** Mathias Heusser

---

## Description

User wants to type custom tolerance values like "-21.3 / +2.9" instead of using predefined options. Current input doesn't allow free text entry.

---

## Affected Area

Feature assignment
```

---

### Example 2: User research insight

**Title:** Understand how programmers handle multi-setup parts

**Labels:** `design`, `research`, `Prio 2`

```markdown
## Source

üî¨User research / Feedback

**Client:** ‚Äî
**Reported by:** Maji

---

## Description

We need to understand how CNC programmers currently handle parts that require multiple setups. This will inform the design of our multi-setup workflow.

**Research goals:**

- How do they decide setup order?
- What information do they need per setup?
- Pain points with current CAM tools?

---

## Affected Area

Operation Management
```

---

### Example 3: Feature design from product discovery

**Title:** Design batch tool replacement flow

**Labels:** `design`, `feature-design`, `Prio 1`

```markdown
## Source

üí° Product discovery

**Client:** ‚Äî
**Reported by:** Maji

---

## Description

Design a flow that allows users to replace a tool across multiple projects at once. Should include:

- Project selection
- Preview of affected operations
- Confirmation step
- Success/error feedback

---

## Affected Area

Batch Processing

---

## Figma

[link to exploration file]
```

---

### Example 4: Issue with screenshot

**Title:** Box positioning incorrect in PDF viewer

**Labels:** `design`, `improvement`, `Prio 2`

```markdown
## Source

üî¨User research / Feedback

**Client:** Bosch
**Reported by:** Daniel

---

## Description

The OCR bounding boxes are not aligned correctly with the actual dimensions in the PDF. See screenshot below.

---

## Affected Area

PDF Viewer

---

## Screenshot

![Box positioning issue](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/example-image.png)
```

---

## Quick Reference

**Creating an issue checklist:**

1. ‚òê Write clear, concise title
2. ‚òê Add `design` label + type label (e.g., `feature-design`)
3. ‚òê Add priority label if known (`Prio 1`, `Prio 2`, or `Prio 3`) ‚Äì optional
4. ‚òê Select source (Client / Engineering / Research / Product discovery)
5. ‚òê Add client name if applicable
6. ‚òê Write short description
7. ‚òê Specify affected area
8. ‚òê Add Figma section only if there's a link (omit entirely if none)
9. ‚òê Add screenshot if helpful (drag & drop into GitHub)

